rComments: A very energy-intensive course with many lab reports which are worth too few marks for the extensive research and time-commitment required, and without clear grading criteria. Cyr is a good lecturer and the questions on the final were not unreasonable, although somewhat stringently marked. Unfortunately, the course is highly disorganized.
MISSED MY 5% ASSIGNMENT WHEN RELEASING ACORN FINAL GRADE... HARD MARKING ON FINAL EXAM
Lab reports due every week... Get ready to use a chunk of your time to write them.

I thought lab writeups were long. Lectures were fun. Helene can be vague in explaining concepts, but I liked her enthusiasm. What she puts on the test is skimmed over in class. You should study using past tests. If I took this again, I would bring my laptop and type comments over PPT slides instead of writing on blank sheets of paper.

Lectures overloaded with detail (30 slides in 40 mins) - felt I was taking a 2-semester course in 8 wks. TOO MUCH FIELD/LAB WORK & REPORTS for too few marks!! Workload way heavier than it should be for a 2nd-yr course; hard marking with 4th-yr/grad expectations on written work; 40% final exam.
really wants her students to fail, looks very smug when describing that she will not make the final exam easy. group projects suck, labs are marked hard, she is not cool.

rComments: Thought she was a great Prof! Had her for another class as well.  She talks a lot but it's always relative and seems like she's involved with the subject. Her office hours are worth the visit. She's always willing to explain her lecture over again, but come with questions!

A truly terrible teacher; talks incredibly fast, is unclear (at times I wonder if she's just trying to get through her lecture being as vague as possible) and spends an excessive amount of time talking about irrelevant or pointless details while racing through the material that will actually be tested. By far the worst of the BIO150 profs in 06/07.
she was a pretty good prof. Speed of lecture was good, and she wasn't boring.
